title: 221b Baker St.
content: November 1895. London is shrouded in fog and Sherlock Holmes and Watson pass time restlessly awaiting a new case.

title: Aldgate Station
content: Arthur Cadogan West was found dead, head crushed in on train tracks at Aldgate Station at 6AM Tuesday morning.

title: Eiffel Tower
content: The Eiffel Tower is an iconic symbol of Paris, attracting nearly 7 million visitors each year.

title: Statue of Liberty
content: The Statue of Liberty is a symbol of freedom and democracy, standing tall in New York Harbor.

title: Shibuya Crossing
content: Shibuya Crossing is one of the busiest intersections in the world, located in Tokyo.

title: Opera House
content: The Sydney Opera House is a multi-venue performing arts centre, famous for its unique design.

title: Christ the Redeemer
content: Christ the Redeemer is a colossal statue of Jesus Christ, overlooking the city of Rio de Janeiro.
